        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 6:27PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Matheson, or 13 miles west of Limon, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Hail may
accumulate on roadways causing hazardous travel.

Locations impacted include...
Cedar Point.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 343 and 354.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
